<p>I want to send some data from my chrome extension to my server. In my chrome extension, I do this:</p>  <pre><code>var data_to_send =     'data=' + encodeURIComponent(main_data) +     '&amp;uid=' + encodeURIComponent(uid) +     '&amp;ct='  + encodeURIComponent(ct);  var xhr = new XMLHttpRequest(); xhr.open('POST', HOST+'/data?', true); xhr.onreadystatechange = function() {     if (xhr.readyState == 4) {         if (xhttp.status == 200)             DB('Data SENT!');         else             DB('retry to send the data...')     } } xhr.send(data_to_send); </code></pre>  <p>What should I do at the server end to receive and store this data?</p>